On December 20, 2022, the President signed several laws designating various facilities in honor of individuals and reauthorizing programs. These include the Richard A. Pittman VA Clinic in French Camp, California, the Lt. Col. Luke Weathers, Jr. VA Medical Center in Memphis, Tennessee, the Major General Oliver W. Dillard VA Clinic in Canton, Michigan, and the Sy Kaplan VA Clinic in Palm Desert, California. Additionally, the Ron Wright Post Office Building in Arlington, Texas, the James D. Todd United States Courthouse in Jackson, Tennessee, and the Paul D. Wellstone Federal Building in Minneapolis, Minnesota were also designated. Lastly, the Early Hearing Detection and Intervention Act of 2022 was reauthorized, along with the Paul D. Wellstone Building Act of 2022. The President expressed gratitude to the representatives, senators, and delegations for their leadership in these matters.